The function f(n)=f(n-1)+n, f(0)=0 and the function r(n)=g(n)-r(n-1), g(n)=g(n-1)+2n-1, r(0)=0, g(0)=0. are symbolically distinct, yet extensionally equal. Both functions output equal values for every n. Thus they are equal functions, f(n)=r(n).
